result.formatted_address: 1 Expo Dr, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: Golden Bauhinia Square

reviews.text:
You can have a good view here as Victoria Harbour is in front of you. You can relax and seat here.
There are lots of cartoon characters for you to take pictures. They are so cute.
In this plaza, you can see flag rising in the morning if its not raining and you are lucky enough.
Very busy, as all the mainland Chinese people come to the attraction. But a very good and interesting statue to look at.

You could get a panoramic view of the Victoria Harbour dazzled with the towering and mountainous backdrop of Kowloon. It is always crowded with tourists all day, especially during the day, so do come over at nightfall for a better view around here. Also, do note that you could experience the light show which sets the Harbour ablaze every night starting from 8 pm, and I could tell you that it's really worth the wait to witness such spectacle here in the heart of Hong Kong!
Very beautiful place...once nearby construction work is completed it will form a combination of tourist places

It's good
A place from where we catch the harbor cruise

result.adr_address: 1 Expo Dr, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 1 Expo Dr, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Centre

reviews.text: Helping people to reach out to other people by hosting exhibitions and conventions, the site is remarkably well maintained and well managed. Never had any problem visiting or Exhibiting there. It will be super convenient to reach when the new subway line opens. 👍

Every year, Hong Kong's book Fair, Winter shopping festival, food Festival are held in this place. Here are a few exhibition halls, one of which is large on the third floor and can accommodate more than 4000 people. On the day of my visit, the Career Expo 2019 was held on the ground floor. It attracted a lot of people to visit.

Great organization!
Every time nothing is missing! The exhibitions are organized in a extraordinary way.
The position is perfect.

Excellent and well organised exhibition hall with modern facilities on multiple floors. A fantastic view of the harbour and building surrounding the convention hall. A very large building needs time to view if your are attending any fairs.
Great place to spend a couple of hours. Since it is next to the sea, the outside is very soothing if you were to sit and enjoy the view.
